\section*{Hypotheses}

\subsection*{Neuron 1}

Based on the raster plots, Neuron 1 appears to exhibit increased
spike density during and immediately following the stimulus window.
This suggests the citronellal odor puff increases the firing rate.

\textbf{Hypothesis:}
The odor stimulus increases firing activity in Neuron 1.

\subsection*{Neuron 2}

Raster plots for Neuron 2 also show clustering of spikes during the
stimulus period.

\textbf{Hypothesis:}
The stimulus increases firing rate in Neuron 2.

\subsection*{Neuron 3}

Neuron 3 shows noticeable gaps in spikes during the stimulus window,
suggesting suppressed activity.

\textbf{Hypothesis:}
The stimulus decreases firing rate in Neuron 3.

