\section*{Model Specification}

To model spike counts we approximate a non-homogeneous Poisson process
by binning time into small intervals.

\[
Y_{it} \sim \text{Poisson}(\lambda_i(t)\Delta t)
\]

Using a log link:

\[
\log(\lambda_i(t)) =
\beta_0 + \beta_1 \cdot \text{stim}(t) + f(t) + b_{\text{trial}}
\]

where

\begin{itemize}
\item $\beta_1$ = stimulation effect (log scale)
\item $f(t)$ = smooth baseline firing pattern
\item $b_{\text{trial}} \sim N(0,\sigma^2)$ = trial random effect
\item $\log(\Delta t)$ = offset term
\end{itemize}

This model allows the firing intensity to vary smoothly in time while
capturing the effect of the stimulus.

